}) {
  return <MDXLayout {...layoutProps} {...props} components={components} mdxType="MDXLayout">

    <p><em parentName="p">{`This page assumes you are comfortable with `}<a parentName="em" {...{
          "href": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Git"
        }}>{`Git`}</a>{`, `}<a parentName="em" {...{
          "href": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Command-line_interface"
        }}>{`Command Line`}</a>{`, and `}<a parentName="em" {...{
          "href": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Npm_(software)"
        }}>{`NPM`}</a>{`. You must have all of these installed on your machine.`}</em></p>
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "what-is-gramble"
    }}>{`What is Gramble?`}</h2>
    <p><a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "https://github.com/littell/gramble_ts"
      }}>{`Gramble`}</a>{` is a TypeScript library, Google Sheets Add-On and command line interface for writing your grammar as a spreadsheet. It is the `}<strong parentName="p">{`recommended`}</strong>{` solution for most WordWeavers.`}</p>
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "adding-your-gramble-model-to-wordweaver"
    }}>{`Adding your gramble model to WordWeaver`}</h2>
    <p>{`Assuming you have made your gramble model and exported it to CSV, you can generate the files necessary for initializing your WordWeaver with the following steps.`}</p>
    <h3 {...{
      "id": "installation"
    }}>{`Installation`}</h3>
    <p>{`You must have the Gramble CLI installed. Install it with npm: `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`npm install -g @gramble/cli`}</inlineCode></p>
    <h3 {...{
      "id": "addedit-wordweaver-keywords-in-your-gramble-model"
    }}>{`Add/edit WordWeaver keywords in your Gramble model`}</h3>
    <p>{`You must ensure that all relevant special keywords for WordWeaver are included in your Gramble model. By default, this includes verb roots (`}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`root`}</inlineCode>{`), pronouns (`}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`agent`}</inlineCode>{` & `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`patient`}</inlineCode>{`), and other options (`}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`option`}</inlineCode>{`). `}</p>
    <p>{`Have a look at the example verbs in a hypothetical Gramble model below - we will illustrate the instructions referring to this example.`}</p>
    <h5 {...{
      "id": "example-verbs"
    }}>{`Example Verbs`}</h5>
    <table>
      <thead parentName="table">
        <tr parentName="thead">
          <th parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": null
          }}>{`text`}</th>
          <th parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": null
          }}>{`gloss`}</th>
          <th parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": null
          }}>{`gloss`}</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody parentName="table">
        <tr parentName="tbody">
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": null
          }}>{`ayaa`}</td>
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": null
          }}>{`be there`}</td>
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": null
          }}>{`VAI`}</td>
        </tr>
        <tr parentName="tbody">
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": null
          }}>{`pashikoo`}</td>
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": null
          }}>{`get up`}</td>
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": null
          }}>{`VAI`}</td>
        </tr>
        <tr parentName="tbody">
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": null
          }}>{`paahpi`}</td>
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": null
          }}>{`laugh`}</td>
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": null
          }}>{`VAI`}</td>
        </tr>
        <tr parentName="tbody">
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": null
          }}>{`ayaa`}</td>
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": null
          }}>{`have`}</td>
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": null
          }}>{`VAIT`}</td>
        </tr>
        <tr parentName="tbody">
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": null
          }}>{`oshiihtaa`}</td>
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": null
          }}>{`make`}</td>
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": null
          }}>{`VAIT`}</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <p>{`Sometimes, this is as simple as just adding the keyword to a pre-existing column header as in:`}</p>
    <h5 {...{
      "id": "example-verbs-with-added-root-keyword"
    }}>{`Example Verbs with added root keyword`}</h5>
    <table>
      <thead parentName="table">
        <tr parentName="thead">
          <th parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": null
          }}>{`text, `}<em parentName="th">{`root`}</em></th>
          <th parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": null
          }}>{`gloss`}</th>
          <th parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": null
          }}>{`gloss`}</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody parentName="table">
        <tr parentName="tbody">
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": null
          }}>{`ayaa`}</td>
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": null
          }}>{`be there`}</td>
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": null
          }}>{`VAI`}</td>
        </tr>
        <tr parentName="tbody">
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": null
          }}>{`pashikoo`}</td>
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": null
          }}>{`get up`}</td>
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": null
          }}>{`VAI`}</td>
        </tr>
        <tr parentName="tbody">
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": null
          }}>{`paahpi`}</td>
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": null
          }}>{`laugh`}</td>
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": null
          }}>{`VAI`}</td>
        </tr>
        <tr parentName="tbody">
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": null
          }}>{`ayaa`}</td>
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": null
          }}>{`have`}</td>
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": null
          }}>{`VAIT`}</td>
        </tr>
        <tr parentName="tbody">
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": null
          }}>{`oshiihtaa`}</td>
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": null
          }}>{`make`}</td>
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": null
          }}>{`VAIT`}</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <p>{`Note that the values here must be unique and there is a conflict here as 'ayaa' occurs twice. In this case, you must create a separate unique identifier:`}</p>
    <h5 {...{
      "id": "example-verbs-with-added-root-keyword-column"
    }}>{`Example Verbs with added root keyword column`}</h5>
    <table>
      <thead parentName="table">
        <tr parentName="thead">
          <th parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": null
          }}>{`text`}</th>
          <th parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": null
          }}>{`gloss`}</th>
          <th parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": null
          }}>{`gloss`}</th>
          <th parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": null
          }}><em parentName="th">{`root`}</em></th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody parentName="table">
        <tr parentName="tbody">
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": null
          }}>{`ayaa`}</td>
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": null
          }}>{`be there`}</td>
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": null
          }}>{`VAI`}</td>
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": null
          }}>{`ayaa-vai`}</td>
        </tr>
        <tr parentName="tbody">
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": null
          }}>{`pashikoo`}</td>
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": null
          }}>{`get up`}</td>
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": null
          }}>{`VAI`}</td>
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": null
          }}>{`pahikoo-vai`}</td>
        </tr>
        <tr parentName="tbody">
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": null
          }}>{`paahpi`}</td>
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": null
          }}>{`laugh`}</td>
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": null
          }}>{`VAI`}</td>
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": null
          }}>{`paahpi-vai`}</td>
        </tr>
        <tr parentName="tbody">
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": null
          }}>{`ayaa`}</td>
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": null
          }}>{`have`}</td>
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": null
          }}>{`VAIT`}</td>
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": null
          }}>{`ayaa-vait`}</td>
        </tr>
        <tr parentName="tbody">
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": null
          }}>{`oshiihtaa`}</td>
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": null
          }}>{`make`}</td>
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": null
          }}>{`VAIT`}</td>
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": null
          }}>{`oshiihtaa-vait`}</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <h3 {...{
      "id": "update-your-wordweaver-configuration"
    }}>{`Update your WordWeaver configuration`}</h3>
    <p>{`Once you have updated your Gramble language model to include all necessary keywords, you can make any necessary changes to your `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "/docs/ww-custom-intro"
      }}>{`WordWeaver Configuration`}</a>{`. You must also add `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`json`}</inlineCode>{` files with your all of your verb roots, pronouns and options. So, the 'Example Verbs' table above might become:`}</p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-json"
      }}>{`[
   {
        "gloss": "be there (vii)",
        "tag": "ashtee-vii"
    },
    {
        "gloss": "melt",
        "tag": "tihkitee-vii"
    },
    {
        "gloss": "be there (vai)",
        "tag": "ayaa-vai"
    },
    {
        "gloss": "get up",
        "tag": "pashikoo-vai"
    },
    {
        "gloss": "laugh",
        "tag": "paahpi-vai"
    },
    {
        "gloss": "have",
        "tag": "ayaa-vait"
    },
    {
        "gloss": "make",
        "tag": "oshiihtaa-vait"
    }
]
`}</code></pre>
    <p>{`You will need to do this for all possible verb roots, pronouns and options.`}</p>
    <h3 {...{
      "id": "exporting-your-conjugations"
    }}>{`Exporting your conjugations`}</h3>
    <p>{`Export your conjugations: `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`gramble generate <yourGrambleFile.csv> --wordweaver > conjugations.json`}</inlineCode></p>
    <h3 {...{
      "id": "initialize-your-wordweaver"
    }}>{`Initialize your WordWeaver`}</h3>
    <p>{`Follow the guide to setting up a new language (`}<em parentName="p">{`...guide forthcoming...`}</em>{`) by moving all of your new files (`}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`verbs.json`}</inlineCode>{`, `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`pronouns.json`}</inlineCode>{`, `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`options.json`}</inlineCode>{` and `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`conjugations.json`}</inlineCode>{`) into your language's folder in the WordWeaver folder. Set the `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`WWLANG`}</inlineCode>{` variable in `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`.env`}</inlineCode>{` to your language's ISO code, or alternatively set it manually in your environment.
Then, ensure your data matches your type definitions by running `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`wordweaver validate-data`}</inlineCode>{`. If all is well, you can `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "/docs/firststeps"
      }}>{`spin up your new WordWeaver `}</a>{`. `}</p>
    <p>{`Congratulations, you're all done!`}</p>
    </MDXLayout>;
}

;
